INSERT INTO `wp_comments` VALUES (380, 1380, 'Edward Eng', 'edward.eng@getchee.com', 'http://www.getchee.com/', '61.230.5.169', '2011-01-13 23:58:54', '2011-01-14 03:58:54', 'Hi Harris,\n\n1A.\nPeople want and need different things. The wealthy segmentation of a population are interested in certain products and services. And their wants and needs are different from those in the middle class and less affluent segmentations. Defining and mapping different segmentations help you understand where each one lives, works, and enjoys entertainment. From here, you understand how to offer certain products and services to certain customers.\n\n1B.\nCompanies have many products and each product has a target customer. But some companies don’t know who their product’s true target customer is. Other companies know who their product’s target customer is, but don’t know where this particular customer lives. Profiling customers, segmenting a population, and dynamically mapping this information helps companies figure out where their product will sell well.\n\n2A.\nYou\'ve profiled and segmented a population to know who likes hamburgers with avocado on them. Now you need to find the hamburgers for them.\n\n2B.\nYou sell hamburgers with avocado on them. Now you need to find people who like the hamburgers you sell.\n\nI hope this was helpful. Let us know if you have more questions. Thanks.', 0, 'post-trashed', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.13) Gecko/20101203 Firefox/3.6.13 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 363, 9); 
