INSERT INTO `wp_comments` VALUES (397, 2319, 'Joshua Roberts', 'joshua.roberts@getchee.com', 'http://www.getchee.com/', '114.32.59.123', '2011-08-01 05:38:30', '2011-08-01 09:38:30', 'Hi Jenn,\r\n\r\nHappy to hear your experience in Thailand has been so great. I\'ve also had nothing but great experiences there; friendly people, amazing food, and amazing laid-back islands.\r\n\r\nI\'ve been in Asia since 2003, primarily in Taipei, Taiwan. It\'s also really great here, for some of the same reasons, and some different. It’s basically my home now, and I love it.\r\n\r\nI\'m wondering what differences you\'ve noticed living in Thailand for the past 4 years. Do you find the city is changing very rapidly, or do you feel it’s slowed down quite a bit? I visit there occasionally and find that there are always new retailers, big brand names I didn’t notice before from back home (The States).\r\n\r\nDo you find yourself missing certain brands that you were accustomed to before heading to Thailand?\r\n\r\nI know for me there are certain things that are a bit harder to find here in Taiwan. For example clothes, I usually stock up when I go back home, partially due to size, and partially due to my weird propensity for brands I love: REI and Banana Republic to name a few.\r\n\r\nIt’s interesting to see over the past decade the amount of multinational brands that have found opportunity in Asian emerging and established markets, and the way they do business out here.', 0, 'post-trashed', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 5.1; rv:5.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/5.0', '', 0, 1); 
