INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2004, 9, '2010-10-13 23:03:54', '2010-10-14 03:03:54', '“No one-size-fits-all approach will work in China, because consumer behavior patterns differ widely across regions and income groups. Managers should tailor their product portfolios to meet local tastes and manage by geographic clusters that cater more effectively to the country’s evolving consumer environments,” state industry experts in a recent article about China’s new pragmatic consumers.\r\n\r\nObviously, this is a challenge when deciding how to expand your brand in shopping malls. Which city do I choose? Where do I have the most market potential? What areas have high levels of saturation?\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/china-mall-segmentation.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2019" title="china-mall-segmentation" src="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/china-mall-segmentation.jpg" alt="" width="512" height="362" /></a></p>\r\nOur most recent shopping mall research highlights some interesting data as a part of providing clearer answers to those questions. For example, it seems that there are lower percentages of high-end malls in cities where there are larger ratios of malls to people such as Nanjing and Shenzhen. However, keep in mind that this might point to signs of higher mall saturation. In that case, focusing on Hangzhou where there are only a handful of malls serving an equally large population as in Nanjing could mean more market potential. All of this is just the tip of the iceberg in helping to formulate effective strategies for expanding in China.\r\n\r\n<a title="Drop us a line." href="http://www.getchee.com/contact.html?utm_source=getchee&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=shopping%2Bmall%2Bsegmentation%2Barticle%2Bcontact%2Blink" target="_blank">Contact us</a> with your problems and questions. We\'ll be sure to answer them.', 'Shopping Mall Segmentation in China', 0, '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'your-brand-which-mall-in-china', '', '\nhttp://blog.getchee.com/?p=1873', '2013-02-25 04:41:12', '2013-02-25 08:41:12', '', 0, 'http://blog.getchee.com/?p=2004', 0, 'post', '', 0, ''); 
