INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2072, 9, '2010-11-10 22:16:56', '2010-11-11 02:16:56', '<h2>Seminar Highlights</h2>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\nThe <em><a title="getchee - business solutions for emerging markets" href="http://www.getchee.com/?utm_source=getchee&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=mall%2Bseminar%2Brecap" target="_blank">getchee</a></em> seminar on targeting profitable malls in China was held on Friday,  October 29. The great turnout created  a fantastic networking and  experience sharing event. We would like to give you a short summary. The  seminar  was  attended by representatives from:\r\n\r\n+ World-leading  sporting goods brands\r\n+ Top hypermarket retailers\r\n+ The number one home furnishings brand\r\n+ Internationally recognized retail brands\r\n<h2>Seminar Summary</h2>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\nTor  Petersen of <a title="eno - lifestyle brand fueled by China\'s youth" href="http://www.eno.cn/zh/about.htm" target="_blank">eno</a> provided great insight on developing a brand in China.  We learned from his mistakes of choosing the wrong locations and what to  look out for in terms of expanding store networks. Additionally, Tor\'s  views on evaluating site selections with regard to building brand  visibiliy and generating profit are valuable lessons for growing in  China.\r\n\r\nJames Grigsby of <em>getchee</em> pointed out that there isn\'t a magic bullet to store level success and  it\'s critical to know where you are in the store network expansion  curve. Most importantly, learn over time and always seek multiple data  inputs.\r\n\r\nJonas  Burstedt presented an inside look of   <a title="IICG - IKEA anchored shopping center developer" href="http://www.iicg.com/" target="_blank">Inter IKEA Center Group</a>\'s  strategy for developing shopping malls in China. Two  case studies of  their upcoming mall openings in Wuxi and Beijing highlighted their key  performance indicators for targeting profitable  mall locations outside  the retail and business centers in the downtown city  areas. Their  knowledge and insight presented strategical drivers for mall   developments.\r\n\r\nPresentation  slides are available in pdf format. To receive a copy or to schedule a   consultation, please feel free to call us anytime at +886.2.7718.0700  or send a message to <a href="mailto:philip.tomlin@getchee.com">philip.tomlin@getchee.com</a>.\r\n<h2>Contact Us</h2>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\nJames Grigsby, SVP getchee Consulting Services\r\nT: +886.2.2766.5100 ext. 103\r\nE: <a href="mailto:james.grigsby@getchee.com">james.grigsby@getchee.com</a>\r\n\r\nHoward Hsiao, VP getchee Enterprise Solutions\r\nT: +886.2.7718.0700 ext. 523\r\nE: <a href="mailto:howard.hsiao@getchee.com">howard.hsiao@getchee.com</a>\r\n\r\nPhilip Tomlin, Business Analyst\r\nT:                                                      +886.2.2766.5100 ext. 126\r\nE: <a href="mailto:philip.tomlin@getchee.com">philip.tomlin@getchee.com</a>', 'Seminar Recap - Target Malls in China', 0, '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'seminar-recap-target-malls-in-china', '', '', '2013-02-20 03:26:04', '2013-02-20 07:26:04', '', 0, 'http://blog.getchee.com/?p=2072', 0, 'post', '', 0, ''); 
