INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2634, 12, '2011-08-01 03:42:14', '2011-08-01 07:42:14', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://www.cpgcorp.com.sg/admin/files/portfolio/travel/New_Phu_Quoc_Airport_Vietnam.jpg" alt="" width="518" height="226" />\r\n\r\nAmid an expected tourism boom, investors from Europe, Thailand, and Malaysia are buying up land and expanding businesses on Phu Quoc, one of Vietnam\'s largest islands and the newest hotspot for international beach seekers.\r\n\r\nThe new investments and expansion come on the heels of the government\'s recently announced plans to fuel a huge boost in tourism; 2 million annual tourists by 2020, up from only 77,000 in 2010.\r\n\r\nPart of the plan includes the investment of US$970 million toward the building of a new international airport for the island which will replace the much smaller one that was originally built in the 1930\'s. Once complete the airport will be capable of handling large aircrafts and will have a capacity of 7 million passengers per year.\r\n\r\nThe focus on boosting growth for local tourist locations reflects the countries much larger ambitions of boosting tourism country-wide.\r\n\r\n"Vision 2030" a tourism authority conference that took place in Hanoi showcased a number of Vietnam\'s new strategy drivers which included supporting brand development and promotion, developing better human resources, better investment infrastructure, and  better international integration. They also stressed the need for more professionalism, modernity, integration, and performance.\r\n\r\nAccording to the strategy for tourism development, revenue from tourism will reach 10-11 billion USD in 2015; 18-19 billion USD  by 2020. Now could be the perfect time for international corporations to look toward Vietnam when considering expansion strategies.\r\n\r\n<a title="Greenfield Market Studies for Asia" href="http://www.getchee.com/services/services-greenfield-market-study.html?utm_source=getchee&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=greenfield%2Bmarket%2Bstudy%2Bfor%2Bvietnam" target="_blank">Take advantage of a Greenfield Market Study and enter the market with confidence.</a>', 'Vietnam Fuels Tourism Industry', 0, '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'vietnam-fuels-tourism-industry', '', '', '2013-02-25 04:40:16', '2013-02-25 08:40:16', '', 0, 'http://blog.getchee.com/?p=2634', 0, 'post', '', 0, ''); 
