INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (3382, 9, '2012-02-01 03:59:04', '2012-02-01 07:59:04', '<strong><a href="mailto:marketing@getchee.com?subject=Interested in ICSC Shopping Mall Workshop" target="_blank"><img class="alignright  wp-image-3437" title="yu-fashion-garden" src="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/yu-fashion-garden.jpg" alt="" width="340" height="242" /></a>Event Information</strong> / <strong>活动信息</strong>\r\nICSC Asia is hosting a workshop to provide shopping mall developers, owners, manager, retailers, architects, consultants, and investors with ideas and best practices for repositioning shopping malls. The event will take place in Shanghai, China and will consist of keynote speakers from INSITE, Starbucks, Bakh Architecture, and getchee.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>本着为购物中心重新定位提出新的理念和最佳方案的初衷，ICSC亚洲为购物中心开发商，业主，经理，零售商，建筑师，顾问和投资商们在中国上海举办了一场研讨会。主讲嘉宾包括： INSITE, Starbucks, Bakh Architecture, and getchee。\r\n\r\n<strong>Event Details</strong> / <strong>活动注册</strong>\r\nDate: February 16, 2012 (Thurs.)\r\nCheck-in: 12:30p.m. to 1:00p.m.\r\nActivities &amp; Topics: 1:00p.m. to 5:45p.m.\r\nVenue: Yueda 889 Center - <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?q=1111%E5%8F%B7+Chang+Shou+Lu,+Jing+An+Qu,+Shanghai,+China,+200042&amp;oe=utf-8&amp;client=firefox-a&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=FdmH3AEd89Y8Bw&amp;split=0&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=1111%E5%8F%B7+Chang+Shou+Lu,+Jing+An+Qu,+Shanghai,+China&amp;t=m&amp;z=17&amp;vpsrc=0&amp;iwloc=A" target="_blank">Map</a>\r\nAddress: 7F, No. 1111, Changshou Road, Jingan District, Shanghai, China\r\nDress Code: Business Casual\r\nRegistration Fee: USD85 / RMB550 for ICSC members, USD120 / RMB760 for non members\r\nInquire: Email Edward Eng at <a href="mailto:marketing@getchee.com?subject=Interested in ICSC Shopping Mall Workshop" target="_blank">marketing@getchee.com</a>\r\n\r\n日期: 2月16日 - 星期四\r\n登记时间: 下午12点半到1点\r\n主题时间: 下午1点到5点45分\r\n地点: 悦达889中心 - <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?q=1111%E5%8F%B7+Chang+Shou+Lu,+Jing+An+Qu,+Shanghai,+China,+200042&amp;oe=utf-8&amp;client=firefox-a&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=FdmH3AEd89Y8Bw&amp;split=0&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=1111%E5%8F%B7+Chang+Shou+Lu,+Jing+An+Qu,+Shanghai,+China&amp;t=m&amp;z=17&amp;vpsrc=0&amp;iwloc=A" target="_blank">地图</a>\r\n地址: 上海市京安区长寿路1111号, 7楼视听室\r\n着装: 商务休闲\r\n费用: ICSC会员85美金/550人民币。非会员120美金/760人民币。\r\n查询: 发送电子邮件给Edward Eng - <a href="mailto:marketing@getchee.com?subject=Interested in ICSC Shopping Mall Workshop" target="_blank">marketing@getchee.com</a><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>1:00 - 1:45 Xu Dajin / 许大金</strong>\r\nRenovating to Reposition a Mall – Yu Fashion Garden Case Study\r\n1. Redevelopment and repositioning and its vital importance to the longevity of shopping centers\r\n2. Multiple impacts of commercial real estate reposition\r\n3. Interpreting successes and failures of shopping center repositioning and renovation\r\n4. How success depends on sound operating systems for:\r\n- Developing leasing tools and strategies\r\n- Developing repositioning strategies\r\n- Developing portfolio formulas\r\n\r\n重新定位重建购物中心 – 豫城时尚案例分析\r\n1. 购物中心的重新规划及定位，是购物中心永恒的核心\r\n2. 商业地产重新规划及定位的多重裂变\r\n3. 解读购物中心重新规划及定位的成败依据\r\n4. 基于营运体系的招商是成功的关键\r\n－ 招商工具的制定及策略\r\n－ 定位策略\r\n－ 业态组合策略注定了成败\r\n\r\n<a href="mailto:marketing@getchee.com?subject=Interested in ICSC Shopping Mall Workshop" target="_blank"><img title="xu-dajin" src="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/xu-dajin1.jpg" alt="" width="99" height="80" /></a>\r\nXu Dajin has a wealth of experience in real estate development. Prior to joining to INSITE，Mr. Xu was Deputy General Manager of Hong Kong SPACE Creative Holdings Limited where he led leasing and investment planning and project operations promotion. Prior to that, Mr. Xu was in senior management of SOHO China, Beijing Lanse Gangwan Property Development and Beijing Xiao Xijun Real Estate Development.\r\n\r\n许大金于 2011年8月1日加入盈石，担任营运统筹及管理中心高级总监一职；履新前，他曾就职于香港SPACE商业管理集团的副总经理，负责招商规划，统筹及项目 的运营推广。在地产零售行业领域有着非常丰富的工作经验；他曾是SOHO中国有限公司，北京蓝色港湾置业有限公司，北京新奥西郡房地产开发有限公司的企业 高管。同时，许也是现任中国商业联合会购物中心专业委员会专家委员，中国房地产经理人联盟商业地产专业委员会主任，清华大学国际商业地产运营商的培训讲 师。\r\n\r\n<strong>1:45 - 2:45 Andy Adams</strong>\r\nImplementing Repositioning with Your Retail Partner\r\n5 Key Issues for Tenants During Redevelopments\r\n1. Timing and Notice\r\n2. Financial Impacts\r\n3. Customer Impacts\r\n4. Staging of the Redevelopment / Temporary Space Space\r\n5. Outcomes (new position, customers, tenant mix, brands, etc)\r\n\r\n与您的零售合作伙伴推行重新定位\r\n重建项目时租户关注的5个要点\r\n1. 重建的时间及预先通知\r\n2. 财务上的影响\r\n3. 对顾客的影响\r\n4. 重建过程／临时空间\r\n5. 重建的结果（新的定位、顾客、租户、品牌等）\r\n\r\n<a href="mailto:marketing@getchee.com?subject=Interested in ICSC Shopping Mall Workshop" target="_blank"><img title="andy-adams" src="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/andy-adams1.jpg" alt="" width="99" height="80" /></a>\r\nAndy Adams is responsible for developing, leading and executing the strategy for new store development up to 1,500 stores in China by 2015, as well as managing the existing +500 store portfolio to enhance customers’ in-store experience. For the three years prior to joining the China team, Andy was vice president, Store Development, for the Asia Pacific region which included 10 businesses stretching from South Korea to New Zealand. Andy started his eight-year career with Starbucks in Canada and held the position of director of Existing Stores and Portfolio there. He has also participated in numerous store development projects for the North America market.\r\n\r\nAndy Adams 负责制定、领导并实施星巴克中国的新门店开发策略，以实现公司到2015年在中国拥有1500家门店的目标。同时，Andy还负责管理星巴克中国现有的 500家门店，提升消费者在门店内的体验。2008年至2011年间，Andy曾担任星巴克亚太区门店开发副总裁，负责亚太区从韩国至新西兰的10余个市 场的门店开发业务。Andy在星巴克的职业生涯始于8年前，时任星巴克加拿大现有门店管理部门的总监。任期内，他还参与了星巴克在北美市场的多个门店开发 项目。\r\n\r\n<strong>2:45 - 3:00</strong>\r\nBreak / 休息\r\n\r\n<strong>3:00 - 4:00 Reja Bakh</strong>\r\nRejuvenating the Surrounding Community – How a Mall Brings Economic Benefits to Area Redevelopment Initiatives\r\nUsing the six step market analysis to guide building design and user experience:\r\n1. Property productivity analysis\r\n2. Market delineation\r\n3. Demand analysis\r\n4. Supply analysis\r\n5. Analyze interaction of supply and demand\r\n6. Subject market capture and risk analysis\r\n\r\n振兴旧区 – 购物中心如何为整体重建计划带来经济效益？\r\n使用六步市场分析来指导建筑设计及购物者的体验:\r\n1. 物业生产力分析\r\n2. 市场圈定\r\n3. 需求分析\r\n4. 供应分析\r\n5. 分析供求的相互作用\r\n6. 主体的市场捕捉和风险分析\r\n\r\n<a href="mailto:marketing@getchee.com?subject=Interested in ICSC Shopping Mall Workshop" target="_blank"><img title="reja-bakh" src="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/reja-bakh1.jpg" alt="" width="99" height="80" /></a>\r\nReja Bakh holds a master of architecture from Cornell University / MIT.  Mr Bakh has over 21 years’ experience in New York working with Richard Meier Architects and Gwathemy Segal Architects; in the course of this, Mr Bakh developed a strong internationally diverse portfolio in the United States, Italy, Germany and China in residential, hospitality, mixed-use and campus design. Projects ranged in size from small scale product design to the 6 million square foot headquarters campus of one of China’s top 10 largest companies.  Mr. Bakh’s extensive experience in China includes working on the Pudong master plan (Hengmian Old Town), North Hongqiao master plan, North Bund master plan and many other projects that have since household names.\r\n\r\nReja Bakh是BAKH Architecture上海办事处的首席设计总监；拥有康奈尔大学/麻省理工学院的建筑硕士学位，并享有辉煌的事业。他在纽约拥有超过21年的工作经 验， 透过与Richard Meier Architects和Gwathemy Segal Architects两家建筑事务所的合作，在美国，意大利，德国及中国等地，从事过住宅，酒店，多用途项目和机构建筑设计，项目规模从小型的产品设计到 600万平方尺的中国十大企业总部建筑。Bakh的丰富中国阅历，包括横沔老城浦东新区总体规划，北虹桥总体规划，北外滩总体规划，以及许多家喻户晓的项 目。\r\n\r\n<strong>4:00 - 5:00 James Grigsby</strong>\r\nUnderstanding Economic and Other Advantages of Catchment Areas – Developing Malls That Brings New Streams of Revenue into Them\r\n- Calculating an effective catchment area\r\n- Static and dynamic makeup of catchment area population\r\n- Identifying the optimal retail brands for siting in the property\r\n- Using a market retail index to determine the area’s potential for retailers and brands\r\n\r\n了解周边经济状况及优势, 开发能够带来新收入来源的购物中心\r\n－ 计算服务范围的效益\r\n－ 服务范围人口的静态和动态组成\r\n－ 为物业选择最理想的零售品牌\r\n－ 利用市场零售指数确定某地区对零售商和品牌的潜力\r\n\r\n<a href="mailto:marketing@getchee.com?subject=Interested in ICSC Shopping Mall Workshop" target="_blank"><img title="james-grigsby" src="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/james-grigsby1.jpg" alt="" width="99" height="80" /></a>\r\nJames Grigsby heads operations for getchee’s consulting services – the leading provider of retail/commercial predictive analytics and location intelligence data in the Asia Pacific region.  Mr. Grigsby has helped a range of financial services and retail firms boost their profitability through better aligning sales and distribution resources with location-driven demand patterns. His clients included HSBC, Standard Chartered Bank, Nike, VF Corp., Yum! Brands, and Watsons personal care stores. James has a master’s degree in international management from the University of California, San Diego.\r\n\r\nJames Grigsby领导getchee咨询服务在台北及上海的业务，getchee在亚太地区的零售／商业预测分析及店址数据信息领域上拥有领导地位。 James曾经协助金融服务机构和零售公司根基由地点带动的需求模式，重组销售和分销资源， 从而提高盈利。他的客户包括汇丰银行、渣打银行、耐克、VF Corp、Yum!、屈臣氏等。James拥有圣地亚哥加州大学国际管理硕士学位。\r\n\r\n<strong>5:00 - 5:45</strong>\r\nInteractive Discussion / 互动讨论\r\n\r\n<a href="mailto:marketing@getchee.com?subject=Interested in ICSC Shopping Mall Workshop" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3450" title="edward-eng" src="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/edward-eng.jpg" alt="" width="99" height="80" /></a>\r\nInquire: Email Edward Eng at <a href="mailto:marketing@getchee.com?subject=Interested in ICSC Shopping Mall Workshop" target="_blank">marketing@getchee.com</a>\r\n查询: 发送电子邮件给Edward Eng - <a href="mailto:marketing@getchee.com?subject=Interested in ICSC Shopping Mall Workshop" target="_blank">marketing@getchee.com</a>', 'Join Us at ICSC\'s Shopping Mall Reposition and Renovation Workshop ', 0, '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'join-us-at-icscs-shopping-mall-reposition-and-renovation-workshop', '', '', '2013-02-20 03:23:49', '2013-02-20 07:23:49', '', 0, 'http://blog.getchee.com/?p=3382', 0, 'post', '', 6, ''); 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (3468, 9, '2012-03-07 21:39:50', '2012-03-08 01:39:50', '<strong><a href="http://events.getchee.com/networking-event-mar28-2012/index.html" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3471" title="beijing-international-hotel" src="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/beijing-international-hotel.jpg" alt="" width="526" height="250" /></a></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>World Retail Congress Asia Pacific - March 28 to 29, Beijing, China</strong>\r\nThe inaugural World Retail Congress Asia Pacific, launched in 2011 in Hong Kong, was an incredible success, attracting more than 400 attendees and an outstanding line-up of speakers who brought regional and international insight into how to build strong retail businesses in these fast growing markets. The Congress also proved to be a powerful platform for CEOs to meet and network. 2012 will see the Congress move to Beijing, capital of one of the world\'s most exciting and fast-growing marketplaces. Click <a href="http://events.getchee.com/networking-event-mar28-2012/index.html" target="_blank">here</a> for more.\r\n\r\n<strong>Venue</strong>\r\nBeijing International Hotel - <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?q=%E5%8C%97%E4%BA%AC%E4%B8%9C%E5%9F%8E%E5%8C%BA%E5%BB%BA%E5%9B%BD%E9%97%A8%E5%86%85%E5%A4%A7%E8%A1%979%E5%8F%B7&amp;um=1&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=0x35f1ad305bee67e1:0x1bf43a3001228866,9%E5%8F%B7+Jian+Guo+Men+Nei+Da+Jie,+Dong+Cheng+Qu,+Bei" target="_blank">Map</a>\r\nNo.9 Jiangguo Mennei Street\r\nBeijing, China\r\n\r\n<strong>Event Details</strong>\r\nDate: March 28 - 29, 2012 (Wed. – Thurs.)\r\nCheck-in: 08:00\r\nActivities &amp; Topics: Starts at 08:30 on Wednesday\r\nVenue: Beijing International Hotel\r\nAddress: No.9 Jiangguo Mennei Street, Beijing, China\r\nDress Code: Business\r\nReg. Fee: Visit <a href="http://www.worldretailcongressasia.com/" target="_blank">World Retail Congress\'s Asia Pacific site</a>. Enter dis-getchee-25 to save 25%.\r\n\r\n<strong>Event Highlights</strong>\r\nJames Grigsby, SVP of getchee Consulting Services, is a panelist for the Winning Store Planning and Design session on Wednesday, March 28 at 14:15.  This session offers insights into how retailers can use their stores to surprise, engage, and delight their customers. It’ll also focus on best practices regarding location planning and customer analytics to drive shopper engagement and retail strategies. To set up a meeting with James during the event in advance, please fill out the form on <a href="http://events.getchee.com/networking-event-mar28-2012/index.html" target="_blank">this page</a>. Thanks.', 'Join Us at World Retail Congress Asia Pacific 2012 - Beijing, China', 0, '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'join-us-at-world-retail-congress-asia-pacific-2012-beijing-china', '', '', '2013-02-20 03:23:49', '2013-02-20 07:23:49', '', 0, 'http://blog.getchee.com/?p=3468', 0, 'post', '', 0, ''); 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (3492, 9, '2012-03-08 21:24:33', '2012-03-09 01:24:33', '<strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3493" title="palm-springs-convention-center" src="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/palm-springs-convention-center.jpg" alt="" width="520" height="200" /></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Partner Conference - March 24 to 27, Palm Springs, CA\r\n</strong>The Esri Partner Conference is part summit, part jamboree. It\'s the yearly meeting place of Esri\'s global partners and distributors that are reshaping the world through the application of geospatial technology. At the Esri Partner Conference, we celebrate their efforts and provide them with the environment to develop the strategies and skills that will extend the value of their business and further demonstrate the power of geographic information to deliver success. Click <a href="http://events.getchee.com/networking-event-mar24-2012/index.html" target="_blank">here</a> for more.\r\n\r\n<strong>Developer Summit</strong><strong> - March 26 to 29, Palm Springs, CA</strong>\r\nThe DevSummit features user presentations detailing GIS success stories, technical sessions on hot topics and new software functionality, and one-on-one advice from Esri development staff. The Esri Developer Summit (DevSummit) is an annual gathering of developers who want to learn what tools are available for creating mapping applications or adding mapping capabilities to existing applications. Click <a href="http://events.getchee.com/networking-event-mar26-2012/index.html" target="_blank">here</a> for more.', 'Meet Us at ESRI\'s Partner Conference and Developer Summit', 0, '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'meet-us-at-esris-partner-conference-and-developer-summit', '', '', '2013-02-21 04:52:02', '2013-02-21 08:52:02', '', 0, 'http://blog.getchee.com/?p=3492', 0, 'post', '', 0, ''); 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (3519, 9, '2012-05-03 21:41:17', '2012-05-04 01:41:17', '<a href="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/newsletter-may1-2012-top1.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3524" title="capitamalls-beijing" src="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/capitamalls-beijing.jpg" alt="" width="526" height="227" /></a>\r\n\r\nSingapore-based shopping center developer CapitaMalls Asia recently said it would spend US$365 million to develop a mall in southern Beijing, buying the land from a subsidiary of the Poly Real Estate Group.\r\n\r\nThe development will feature a seven-story, 122,000-square-meter mall, representing a total cost of around RMB$19,190 per square meter for construction and land, the company stated. The project is due for completion in 2015.\r\n\r\nCapitaMalls Asia, 65 percent owned by Temasek, is one of the most active international property developers in China. This will be its 57th mall in the country.\r\n\r\nLet\'s take a look at the differences between the areas surrounding this mall and a popular CapitaMall in central Beijing.\r\n\r\n<strong>CapitalMalls Xizhimen in Central Beijing</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/newsletter-may1-2012-middle.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3527" title="capitamalls-central-bejing" src="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/capitamalls-central-bejing.jpg" alt="" width="526" height="227" /></a>\r\n\r\nHousehold\r\n890,869\r\n\r\nEmployed Population\r\n981,028\r\n<strong>\r\nCapitamalls Tiangongyuan in Southern Beijing</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/newsletter-may1-2012-bottom.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3531" title="capitamalls-southern-bejing" src="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/capitamalls-southern-bejing.jpg" alt="" width="526" height="227" /></a>\r\n\r\nHousehold\r\n46,693\r\n\r\nEmployed Population\r\n43,803\r\n\r\nIs this really the new retail hotspot in Beijing? <a href="mailto:curious@getchee.com?subject=May%203,%202012%20Newsletter%20Inquiry%20Blog" target="_blank">Contact us </a>to learn more about this area using getchee data, tools, and services.', 'A Deeper Look at CapitaMalls in Beijing', 0, '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-deeper-look-at-capitamalls-in-beijing', '', '', '2013-02-25 04:11:02', '2013-02-25 08:11:02', '', 0, 'http://blog.getchee.com/?p=3519', 0, 'post', '', 0, ''); 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (3539, 9, '2012-05-08 21:26:52', '2012-05-09 01:26:52', '<a href="http://www.getchee.com/products/kiwi-overview.html?utm_source=getchee&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=kiwi%2Bicsc%2B2012" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3543" title="kiwi-icsc-2012" src="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/kiwi-icsc-2012.jpg" alt="" width="526" height="227" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Introducing Kiwi</strong>\r\nWe\'re excited to demo <a href="http://www.getchee.com/products/kiwi-overview.html?utm_source=getchee&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=kiwi%2Bicsc%2B2012" target="_blank">Kiwi</a> this year. We developed Kiwi to visualize business and market data on a map for better validation, communication, and discovery. Find out how Kiwi can help expand and optimize your business in Asia.\r\n\r\n<strong>Kiwi Product Demo Session</strong>\r\n<a href="http://exhibits.icsc.org/2012MPM/public/floorplan.aspx?MapID=129&amp;BoothID=150214&amp;Booth=319" target="_blank">Product Demo Theater</a>\r\nMonday, May 21\r\n1:30-1:50pm\r\nWe\'d love to meet you.<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>getchee Booth</strong>\r\n<a href="http://exhibits.icsc.org/2012MPM/public/floorplan.aspx?MapID=129&amp;BoothID=150214&amp;Booth=319" target="_blank">Booth 319</a>\r\nMarketplace Mall\r\nMay 20 - 22\r\n<a href="mailto:edward.eng@getchee.com?subject=ICSC%20Vegas%202012%20Meeting%20Request" target="_blank">Schedule a meeting.</a>', 'Discover Asia with Kiwi at ICSC 2012', 0, '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'discover-asia-with-kiwi-at-icsc-2012', '', '', '2013-02-20 03:20:37', '2013-02-20 07:20:37', '', 0, 'http://blog.getchee.com/?p=3539', 0, 'post', '', 0, ''); 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (3632, 88890, '2012-06-20 22:19:14', '2012-06-21 02:19:14', 'In <a href="http://blog.getchee.com/?p=3621" target="_blank">the last post</a>, we delved into Burberry\'s past and compared it to what they have planned for the future. This week, we present you with a closer look at where Burberry has stores and how they relate to the retail market potential in each province. This should give you a better picture of where potential for growth lies. If you\'re interested in more info on these areas, feel free to shoot us an <a href="mailto:curious@getchee.com?subject=June%2020,%202012%20Newsletter%20Inquiry%20Blogpost" target="_blank">email</a>.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->', 'Burberry in China', 0, '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-does-burberry-stack-up-to-chinas-retail-market-potential', '', '\nhttp://blog.getchee.com/?p=3621', '2013-02-21 04:39:43', '2013-02-21 08:39:43', '', 0, 'http://blog.getchee.com/?p=3632', 0, 'post', '', 1, ''); 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (3862, 9, '2012-09-14 04:32:18', '2012-09-14 08:32:18', '<a title="MIPIM Asia – The premium real estate show for professionals in Asia" href="http://www.mipim.com/en/mipim-asia/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3864" title="mipim-asia-2012" src="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/mipim-asia-2012.jpg" alt="" width="526" height="194" /></a>\r\n\r\nA key commercial real estate show for professionals in Asia, MIPIM Asia is a 3-in-1 real estate fair, including dedicated <a title="Investors: Key Reasons to Attend MIPIM Asia" href="http://www.mipim.com/en/mipim-asia/discover-mipim-asia/investment-summit/" target="_blank">investment</a> and <a title="Retailers: Key Reasons to Attend MIPIM Asia" href="http://www.mipim.com/en/mipim-asia/discover-mipim-asia/retail-summit/" target="_blank">retail</a> conferences and a diverse exhibition zone.\r\n\r\n<a title="MIPIM Asia Awards: Cast your vote!" href="http://www.mipim.com/en/mipim-asia/programme/mipim-asia-awards-voting/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3868" title="mipim-asia-your-choice-award" src="http://blog.getchee.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/mipim-asia-your-choice-award.jpg" alt="" width="526" height="141" /></a>\r\n\r\nAlso, cast your vote for the Your Choice Award. Pick your favorite real estate project in Asia for a chance to win a free iPad.', 'Join Us at MIPIM Asia 2012', 0, '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'join-us-at-mipim-asia-2012', '', '', '2013-02-20 03:20:37', '2013-02-20 07:20:37', '', 0, 'http://blog.getchee.com/?p=3862', 0, 'post', '', 0, ''); 
